  <h2><a href="../../expert/robert-kapp" title="Robert Kapp">Robert Kapp</a></h2>

  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <div class="field field-type-filefield field-field-image">
    <div class="field-items">
            <div class="field-item odd">
                    <img src="../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/Robert_Kapp_0.jpg" alt="" title="" width="100" height="100" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/>        </div>
        </div>
</div>
<p>For ten years, Robert Kapp was president of the U.S.-China Business Council (USCBC), the preeminent organization of American companies involved in U.S.-China investment and trade.   As leader of the USCBC, he engaged extensively with U.S. and Chinese government leaders and key agencies on a wide range of policy issues, including questions of strong interest on Capitol Hill.</p>
